author: news.com.au
title: Daily earnings results round-up
text:
RESULTS ROUND-UP
ASALEO CARE
Summary: The company behind Sorbent toilet paper and Libra tampons said lower manufacturing costs helped overcome increasing competition and lift half year profit. Profit: $32.5m, up from $28.2m BC IRON Summary: Weaker iron ore prices and related writedowns on mining assets dragged the junior miner into the red for the year. Loss: $159.5m, down from a $71.9m profit DRILLSEARCH Summary: Slumping oil prices resulted in writedowns on the energy producer and explorer's assets in the year, while revenue also fell. Loss: $8.1m, down from a $42m profit ORORA Summary: The packaging company spun-off from Amcor lifted full year earnings in its Australasian operations, and forecast continued growth. Profit: $131.4m up from $104.4m SEVEN GROUP Summary: The owner of the Westrac mining services reduced the value of several businesses in the year, and it fears further slides in earnings as the resources industry cuts costs. Loss: $359.1m, down from a $262.5m profit WESTFIELD CORPORATION Summary: Reporting its first half year report since the demerger of its Australian and NZ businesses in 2014, the US-focused shopping centre operator said the move has delivered benefits. Profit: $US465.9m WORLEYPARSONS Summary: The engineering and construction giant swung into the red due to impairments and costs of a legal settlement, while annual revenue fell due to weaker commodity market activity. Loss: $54.9m, down from a $249.1m profit
